00:17:57,933 --> 00:17:58,500
Morning.

274
00:17:59,200 --> 00:18:00,733
I did just wake up.

275
00:18:01,567 --> 00:18:03,300
Xiang Lang also needs to rent a place now that he's back.

276
00:18:03,300 --> 00:18:04,633
Maybe you two could be roommates?

277
00:18:08,667 --> 00:18:10,033
I forgot to tell you

278
00:18:10,100 --> 00:18:11,400
but I found a roommate.

279
00:18:11,467 --> 00:18:12,267
Who is it?

280
00:18:16,100 --> 00:18:17,600
Should we pick a day

281
00:18:18,100 --> 00:18:19,000
to hang out together?

282
00:18:19,100 --> 00:18:20,300
We definitely should.

283
00:18:20,467 --> 00:18:21,367
It's been years.

284
00:18:21,867 --> 00:18:22,633
How about Thursday?

285
00:18:22,633 --> 00:18:23,767
I'm not working that day.

286
00:18:23,800 --> 00:18:24,967
Just don't bail on us.

287
00:18:24,967 --> 00:18:26,733
Don't worry. I won't.

288
00:18:26,800 --> 00:18:27,800
Thursday it is then.

289
00:18:28,033 --> 00:18:28,533
Bye.

290
00:18:29,367 --> 00:18:30,000
Bye.

291
00:18:30,633 --> 00:18:31,300
Love you.

292
00:18:40,100 --> 00:18:40,967
Are you going out?

293
00:18:43,000 --> 00:18:44,167
My old friend, Xiang Lang

294
00:18:46,000 --> 00:18:47,000
is back in the country.

295
00:18:48,100 --> 00:18:50,000
We were in Class 17 in high school

296
00:18:50,033 --> 00:18:51,500
and he and Qiao were in Class 15.

297
00:18:52,800 --> 00:18:53,500
The three of us

298
00:18:53,500 --> 00:18:55,100
grew up together in kindergarten.

299
00:18:56,467 --> 00:18:57,467
You must know him, right?

300
00:19:00,300 --> 00:19:00,933
It doesn't ring a bell.

301
00:19:11,667 --> 00:19:13,433
Have you picked a spot for the gathering?

302
00:19:13,867 --> 00:19:14,633
Not yet.

303
00:19:17,567 --> 00:19:19,633
How about Overtime?

304
00:19:20,500 --> 00:19:21,267
Since we're roommates

305
00:19:21,267 --> 00:19:22,567
you can help bring in more customers.

306
00:19:24,400 --> 00:19:25,567
Has your business gotten so bad

307
00:19:26,367 --> 00:19:28,500
that you need to personally bring in customers?

308
00:19:30,000 --> 00:19:32,067
I've told you before that it's not making much money.

309
00:19:32,067 --> 00:19:33,633
We have to find ways to promote it

310
00:19:33,633 --> 00:19:34,433
and get more customers.

311
00:19:39,067 --> 00:19:39,633
What do you think?

312
00:19:44,467 --> 00:19:45,733
I can give you a roommate discount.

313
00:19:47,567 --> 00:19:48,267
What's the discount?

314
00:19:50,767 --> 00:19:51,833
Let's say

315
00:19:55,400 --> 00:19:55,933
1 percent.

316
00:19:57,300 --> 00:19:58,033
Come again?

317
00:19:58,300 --> 00:19:58,967
1 percent.

318
00:20:03,867 --> 00:20:04,833
How generous.

319
00:20:05,667 --> 00:20:06,467
I'll consider it.

320
00:20:06,467 --> 00:20:07,267
It's decided then.

321
00:20:07,600 --> 00:20:08,600
Thursday.

322
00:20:09,000 --> 00:20:10,400
I've saved you a spot for Thursday.

323
00:20:19,233 --> 00:20:21,067
Honestly, the first time I went to your gastropub

324
00:20:21,067 --> 00:20:21,867
I spent ages looking for it.

325
00:20:22,100 --> 00:20:24,233
It took me forever to find the Overtime sign.

326
00:20:25,000 --> 00:20:26,067
I didn't exactly want to walk in

327
00:20:28,167 --> 00:20:29,833
looking at it from the outside.

328
00:20:33,167 --> 00:20:33,967
What do you mean?

329
00:20:35,733 --> 00:20:37,400
I just mean the sign isn't obvious

330
00:20:38,167 --> 00:20:39,867
and it doesn't really look like a place to eat.

331
00:20:39,867 --> 00:20:41,000
It looks more like a barbershop.

332
00:20:41,967 --> 00:20:42,467
But of course

333
00:20:42,800 --> 00:20:44,033
that's just my personal opinion.

334
00:20:44,033 --> 00:20:45,100
No need to take it to heart.

335
00:20:49,433 --> 00:20:51,800
Since it was so unnoticeable and so bad

336
00:20:53,367 --> 00:20:54,733
why did you come in the first place?

337
00:21:00,300 --> 00:21:01,000
Headliner.

338
00:21:02,367 --> 00:21:03,467
Oh, it's because you...

339
00:21:05,300 --> 00:21:06,067
I got it.

340
00:21:06,833 --> 00:21:08,067
I'll think about your comment

341
00:21:08,767 --> 00:21:09,567
but I won't change it.

342
00:21:14,867 --> 00:21:15,467
Thursday, okay?

343
00:21:21,133 --> 00:21:21,800
[First News, All Ears for You]

344
00:21:21,800 --> 00:21:22,867
So, here's the story.

345
00:21:23,233 --> 00:21:24,567
Since she's my roommate

346
00:21:24,567 --> 00:21:25,767
I didn't feel right saying no

347
00:21:25,967 --> 00:21:28,233
so I ended up buying these low-quality products from her.

348
00:21:28,767 --> 00:21:30,300
She's clearly taking advantage of me.

349
00:21:30,300 --> 00:21:31,300
I'm going to sue her

350
00:21:31,300 --> 00:21:32,667
and I won't stop until she loses everything.

351
00:21:32,667 --> 00:21:33,433
A 1 percent discount.

352
00:21:34,267 --> 00:21:35,767
Isn't that taking advantage of me, too?

353
00:21:36,367 --> 00:21:38,200
She swindled all my savings away.

354
00:21:38,633 --> 00:21:40,367
I worked for two years to earn that money.

355
00:21:40,400 --> 00:21:41,467
What's the rush?

356
00:21:41,467 --> 00:21:42,733
She took all of it

357
00:21:42,967 --> 00:21:44,000
a total of 50

358
00:21:48,667 --> 00:21:50,267
You seem a bit down recently.

359
00:21:50,467 --> 00:21:51,300
Here's a coffee for you.

360
00:21:52,867 --> 00:21:53,833
Thank you, Mr. Zhang.

361
00:21:54,733 --> 00:21:55,467
No worries.

362
00:21:57,100 --> 00:21:57,800
Eat this

363
00:21:58,067 --> 00:21:58,867
to regain some energy.

364
00:21:59,933 --> 00:22:01,867
Isn't eating not allowed in the cutting room?

365
00:22:01,867 --> 00:22:03,233
I call the shots in this room.

366
00:22:03,467 --> 00:22:04,033
Eat.

367
00:22:05,467 --> 00:22:06,167
Thanks.

368
00:22:08,033 --> 00:22:08,867
This software

369
00:22:08,867 --> 00:22:09,633
has a shortcut key.

370
00:22:09,633 --> 00:22:10,433
Here, let me show you.

371
00:22:20,200 --> 00:22:21,200
What are you doing?

372
00:22:23,667 --> 00:22:24,733
I'm sorry, I...

373
00:22:24,833 --> 00:22:26,633
Sorry, I'll go find someone to clean this up.

374
00:22:28,467 --> 00:22:29,567
Is that necessary?

375
00:22:29,633 --> 00:22:30,933
Everyone knows what you are like.

376
00:22:34,233 --> 00:22:34,733
Let's go.

377
00:22:44,767 --> 00:22:45,300
Wen

378
00:22:45,500 --> 00:22:46,767
you've seen the newspaper today, right?

379
00:22:47,233 --> 00:22:48,267
Your article wasn't included.

380
00:22:48,867 --> 00:22:49,833
Sorry, sir.

381
00:22:50,400 --> 00:22:51,867
I'll keep trying my best.

382
00:22:53,933 --> 00:22:54,967
It's actually quite simple.

383
00:23:00,367 --> 00:23:01,067
Do you know

384
00:23:01,300 --> 00:23:02,167
where

385
00:23:03,233 --> 00:23:04,033
the problem lies?

386
00:23:05,967 --> 00:23:06,733
I know

387
00:23:08,467 --> 00:23:09,467
but I can't do it.

388
00:23:12,400 --> 00:23:13,400
Also, please don't text me

389
00:23:13,400 --> 00:23:15,200
in the middle of the night anymore.

390
00:23:15,867 --> 00:23:16,567
Yifan

391
00:23:17,200 --> 00:23:18,567
why are you here alone?

392
00:23:18,867 --> 00:23:19,833
Are you okay?

393
00:23:27,767 --> 00:23:29,167
Or have you heard about it?

394
00:23:30,100 --> 00:23:31,067
Heard about what?

395
00:23:32,200 --> 00:23:34,433
Lately, everyone's been gossiping about you.

396
00:23:34,600 --> 00:23:36,200
They say when you were at Yihe Daily

397
00:23:36,200 --> 00:23:37,967
the boss's wife came after you

398
00:23:38,233 --> 00:23:39,767
and then the local press blacklisted you.

399
00:23:40,500 --> 00:23:41,633
You couldn't handle it anymore

400
00:23:41,633 --> 00:23:43,300
so you secretly returned to Nanwu.

401
00:23:46,200 --> 00:23:48,067
Those who spread rumors really overestimate me

402
00:23:48,433 --> 00:23:49,567
saying I was blacklisted.

403
00:23:50,733 --> 00:23:53,167
Pretty girls always get caught up in rumors like this.

404
00:23:53,633 --> 00:23:55,467
I've told them that it's definitely not true.

405
00:23:55,733 --> 00:23:57,767
You should go explain it to them quickly.

406
00:23:58,067 --> 00:23:59,800
Do you think they'll believe me even if I explain?

407
00:24:00,600 --> 00:24:02,500
You vixen, wait and see how I deal with you today.

408
00:24:02,833 --> 00:24:03,433
Get out of the way!

409
00:24:04,433 --> 00:24:05,833
You're Wen Yifan, aren't you?

410
00:24:07,567 --> 00:24:08,267
You vixen.

411
00:24:08,267 --> 00:24:09,267
You're the one who sent late-night messages

412
00:24:09,267 --> 00:24:10,300
to flirt with my husband, right?

413
00:24:10,367 --> 00:24:11,100
Shameless!

414
00:24:12,000 --> 00:24:13,300
You shameless wretch!

415
00:24:14,400 --> 00:24:15,400
What are you doing with your phone?

416
00:24:15,400 --> 00:24:16,167
Let me tell you.

417
00:24:16,167 --> 00:24:17,367
I won't believe a word you say today!

418
00:24:17,367 --> 00:24:18,267
Take a good look.

419
00:24:18,800 --> 00:24:20,600
It's your husband who's been sending me messages

420
00:24:20,933 --> 00:24:22,033
and I've never replied with anything inappropriate.

421
00:24:22,033 --> 00:24:23,300
I don't want to hear your nonsense.

422
00:24:23,333 --> 00:24:23,833
You'll see

423
00:24:23,867 --> 00:24:25,100
how I deal with you today.

424
00:24:25,100 --> 00:24:26,633
It takes two to tango.

425
00:24:26,633 --> 00:24:27,667
Keep this up, and you'll make the headlines.

426
00:24:28,300 --> 00:24:29,933
It's clearly the wrongdoer's fault

427
00:24:30,433 --> 00:24:31,467
yet the victim

428
00:24:31,833 --> 00:24:32,667
bears the blame.

429
00:24:32,667 --> 00:24:33,733
Do you really believe

430
00:24:34,033 --> 00:24:36,467
those words were said unconsciously because he was drunk?

431
00:24:36,567 --> 00:24:38,467
I'll write an investigation report and send it

432
00:24:38,867 --> 00:24:39,733
to the president

433
00:24:40,167 --> 00:24:41,967
and the newly formed supervisory committee.

434
00:24:42,300 --> 00:24:43,833
However, I'm not sure

435
00:24:44,500 --> 00:24:45,367
what the result will be.

436
00:24:45,767 --> 00:24:46,500
Why?

437
00:24:46,767 --> 00:24:48,300
He must have his side of the story.

438
00:24:49,300 --> 00:24:50,667
After all, this isn't the first time.

439
00:24:55,667 --> 00:24:57,000
But if you don't say anything

440
00:24:57,267 --> 00:24:58,933
they'll assume you're admitting it.

441
00:24:59,300 --> 00:25:00,167
Whether I admit it or not

442
00:25:00,500 --> 00:25:01,600
they'll only believe

443
00:25:01,600 --> 00:25:02,967
what they want to believe.

444
00:25:04,567 --> 00:25:06,667
Rumors are like wounds.

445
00:25:07,300 --> 00:25:08,433
If you don't pay attention to them

446
00:25:10,200 --> 00:25:11,400
they'll stop hurting after a while.

447
00:25:14,867 --> 00:25:15,900
Don't worry about me.

448
00:25:15,900 --> 00:25:16,567
I'm fine.

449
00:25:17,567 --> 00:25:18,467
What time is it now?

450
00:25:19,833 --> 00:25:20,667
It's almost three o'clock.

451
00:25:21,800 --> 00:25:23,033
I'll go out for an interview now.

452
00:25:26,933 --> 00:25:28,767
All right, Mr. Chen, let's get started.

453
00:25:29,000 --> 00:25:30,367
Could you walk us through

454
00:25:30,367 --> 00:25:32,067
what happened during the incident?

455
00:25:32,633 --> 00:25:33,467
That night

456
00:25:33,733 --> 00:25:34,767
my daughter was helping me out

457
00:25:35,633 --> 00:25:36,867
at the snack stall after school.

458
00:25:37,267 --> 00:25:39,567
Three men at a table were drunk.

459
00:25:40,000 --> 00:25:41,767
My daughter's only sixteen

460
00:25:42,067 --> 00:25:43,800
but they kept harassing her.

461
00:25:44,300 --> 00:25:45,633
At that moment, all I could think

462
00:25:46,000 --> 00:25:47,300
was if they laid a finger on her

463
00:25:47,300 --> 00:25:48,000
I'd...

464
00:25:48,600 --> 00:25:49,267
Dad.

465
00:25:49,433 --> 00:25:50,167
- Are you okay? - Dad.

466
00:25:50,167 --> 00:25:51,033
- Careful. - I'm fine.

467
00:25:51,100 --> 00:25:52,300
Are you all right, Dad?

468
00:25:52,567 --> 00:25:53,933
It's all my fault.

469
00:25:54,133 --> 00:25:56,367
You are hurt because of me.

470
00:25:56,633 --> 00:25:57,933
This injury's nothing.

471
00:25:57,933 --> 00:25:59,033
I'd be heartbroken

472
00:25:59,033 --> 00:26:00,567
if I hadn't kept you safe.

473
00:26:01,167 --> 00:26:02,667
It's because of me.

474
00:26:03,000 --> 00:26:04,367
It's all my fault.

475
00:26:04,367 --> 00:26:05,233
It's not your fault.

476
00:26:07,200 --> 00:26:07,967
Yifan

477
00:26:09,800 --> 00:26:11,367
this child is only sixteen.

478
00:26:12,433 --> 00:26:14,067
Yet their family had to go through such an ordeal.

479
00:26:16,233 --> 00:26:18,467
It's like misfortune always targets the most vulnerable.

480
00:26:21,200 --> 00:26:23,000
But I filmed everything that happened just now.

481
00:26:23,467 --> 00:26:25,300
That kid was crying, and it was heartbreaking.

482
00:26:28,067 --> 00:26:28,800
Wen Yifan?

483
00:26:34,733 --> 00:26:35,733
It really is you.

484
00:26:36,600 --> 00:26:37,600
How come you're back in Nanwu?

485
00:26:38,200 --> 00:26:39,367
I moved back to Nanwu.

486
00:26:39,800 --> 00:26:41,100
- Yifan, maybe I should... - No need.

487
00:26:41,367 --> 00:26:42,233
We're busy right now.

488
00:26:42,233 --> 00:26:43,300
Let's get in touch later.

489
00:26:43,633 --> 00:26:44,400
Who do you think you are?

490
00:26:44,400 --> 00:26:45,833
Who wants to get in touch with you?

491
00:26:46,167 --> 00:26:48,033
Yifan, how about I go back to the car first and sort things out?

492
00:26:48,033 --> 00:26:48,733
You guys can chat.

493
00:26:50,567 --> 00:26:51,200
Thank you.

494
00:26:57,033 --> 00:26:58,167
Why are you back if there's nothing wrong?

495
00:26:59,200 --> 00:27:00,400
Why can't I come back even if nothing's wrong?

496
00:27:01,433 --> 00:27:02,767
I didn't mean it that way.

497
00:27:03,400 --> 00:27:04,233
Don't worry

498
00:27:04,433 --> 00:27:06,300
I won't be staying at your place now that I'm back in Nanwu.

499
00:27:06,833 --> 00:27:08,233
Let's just pretend we never met today.

500
00:27:08,233 --> 00:27:09,867
As long as you don't say anything, no one will know.

501
00:27:10,433 --> 00:27:12,233
I never said you couldn't come to my place.

502
00:27:16,500 --> 00:27:17,267
You didn't.

503
00:27:20,100 --> 00:27:21,900
Why are you being so annoying?

504
00:27:23,867 --> 00:27:24,433
Fine.

505
00:27:24,467 --> 00:27:25,500
I was at fault back then.

506
00:27:25,967 --> 00:27:27,267
I was young and didn't know better.

507
00:27:27,267 --> 00:27:29,267
I was wrong to ask you to leave my house.

508
00:27:29,267 --> 00:27:29,833
All right.

509
00:27:32,000 --> 00:27:33,467
I don't want to bring up the past

510
00:27:33,800 --> 00:27:35,067
nor do I think we need to catch up.

511
00:27:37,067 --> 00:27:38,067
That stuff is heavy, right?

512
00:27:38,467 --> 00:27:39,567
Go check on the patient.

513
00:27:41,367 --> 00:27:42,833
Will you go back home for the Spring Festival?

514
00:27:42,833 --> 00:27:44,000
I have to work during the Spring Festival.

515
00:27:44,733 --> 00:27:46,033
All right, let's add each other on WeChat.

516
00:27:46,033 --> 00:27:46,600
No need.

517
00:27:46,600 --> 00:27:48,067
I just want to live my own life.

518
00:27:49,267 --> 00:27:49,867
You...

519
00:27:52,733 --> 00:27:54,467
My return to Nanwu has nothing to do with anyone.

520
00:27:54,667 --> 00:27:55,800
I won't stay at your place

521
00:27:56,367 --> 00:27:57,500
and it's not because I'm afraid of you.

522
00:28:00,500 --> 00:28:02,567
Every decision I make is for myself.

523
00:28:02,967 --> 00:28:04,100
I'm actually busy. I'll get going now.

524
00:28:10,400 --> 00:28:11,433
Dad, look.

525
00:28:11,433 --> 00:28:13,033
It's snowing outside.

526
00:28:13,933 --> 00:28:15,000
It really is snowing.

527
00:28:15,833 --> 00:28:16,600
Pretty, isn't it?

528
00:28:16,600 --> 00:28:17,367
Yes.

529
00:28:17,567 --> 00:28:18,300
Isn't it lovely?

530
00:28:18,567 --> 00:28:19,267
It is.

531
00:28:19,300 --> 00:28:20,033
Are you happy?

532
00:28:20,033 --> 00:28:20,733
Yes.

533
00:28:20,733 --> 00:28:23,067
Let's have a snowball fight later.

534
00:28:28,033 --> 00:28:29,233
It's snowing.

535
00:28:29,833 --> 00:28:30,633
It's snowing.

536
00:28:31,467 --> 00:28:32,233
Let me lift you up.

537
00:28:37,167 --> 00:28:37,800
Jiang, do you know

538
00:28:37,800 --> 00:28:39,533
how you got your nickname?

539
00:28:40,233 --> 00:28:41,467
I don't.

540
00:28:42,500 --> 00:28:43,433
It's because

541
00:28:44,233 --> 00:28:45,567
you were born

542
00:28:45,867 --> 00:28:48,100
on the day of Frost's Descent.

543
00:28:50,400 --> 00:28:52,067
What exactly is Frost's Descent?

544
00:28:52,233 --> 00:28:53,667
Frost's Descent happens

545
00:28:54,367 --> 00:28:56,433
in late September of the lunar calendar

546
00:28:56,733 --> 00:28:57,967
when the sun

547
00:28:58,267 --> 00:28:59,033
is farther away

548
00:28:59,200 --> 00:29:01,300
from Earth.

549
00:29:01,767 --> 00:29:02,867
It's the day

550
00:29:02,867 --> 00:29:04,400
with the largest temperature difference

551
00:29:05,000 --> 00:29:06,500
between day and night

552
00:29:07,233 --> 00:29:09,000
making the night

553
00:29:09,733 --> 00:29:10,767
particularly cold.

554
00:29:11,467 --> 00:29:13,933
But I'm afraid of the cold.

555
00:29:14,600 --> 00:29:15,633
Don't be afraid, Jiang

556
00:29:16,433 --> 00:29:17,433
I'm here.

557
00:29:17,567 --> 00:29:23,033
ظآزLeaving me lost in the crowdظآز

558
00:29:24,067 --> 00:29:27,900
ظآزBefore we metظآز

559
00:29:28,133 --> 00:29:30,900
ظآزEvery long night was meaninglessظآز

560
00:29:34,933 --> 00:29:36,767
When you're cold, just come to me.

561
00:29:37,267 --> 00:29:38,733
I'll hold you tight

562
00:29:39,167 --> 00:29:40,000
and you won't feel cold anymore.

563
00:29:44,967 --> 00:29:50,467
ظآزThe things we lose will be returned in the endظآز

564
00:29:51,567 --> 00:29:55,367
ظآزAll the detoursظآز

565
00:29:55,767 --> 00:29:58,333
ظآزAre part of the journeyظآز

566
00:29:59,267 --> 00:30:00,667
ظآزWhat was lostظآز

567
00:30:01,167 --> 00:30:04,433
ظآزWill be regainedظآز

568
00:30:06,133 --> 00:30:10,500
ظآزI'll wait for you, so don't worryظآز

569
00:30:12,100 --> 00:30:14,100
ظآزAbout being late.ظآز

570
00:30:29,233 --> 00:30:29,933
Wen Yifan

571
00:30:33,100 --> 00:30:34,133
I have a little flaw

572
00:30:35,200 --> 00:30:35,967
about me.

573
00:30:37,733 --> 00:30:38,600
Only one?

574
00:30:40,967 --> 00:30:43,200
I'm very safety-conscious.

575
00:30:44,000 --> 00:30:45,567
If I don't lock the door before going to bed

576
00:30:46,067 --> 00:30:46,667
I can't sleep.

577
00:30:47,967 --> 00:30:49,367
I always lock the door.

578
00:30:50,100 --> 00:30:51,300
If you're tired, go ahead and sleep.

579
00:30:51,300 --> 00:30:53,000
I'll lock it if I get back late.

580
00:30:53,000 --> 00:30:54,967
I'm talking about before sleeping.

581
00:30:58,067 --> 00:30:59,400
I remember telling you explicitly

582
00:31:00,167 --> 00:31:01,833
before we started sharing the apartment

583
00:31:02,067 --> 00:31:03,200
that I frequently work overtime

584
00:31:03,467 --> 00:31:04,933
and have an irregular routine. You agreed to it.

585
00:31:05,067 --> 00:31:06,067
Then please let me know

586
00:31:06,067 --> 00:31:07,867
in advance

587
00:31:11,167 --> 00:31:12,733
if you're coming back after 10 p.m.

588
00:31:13,400 --> 00:31:14,067
Why?

589
00:31:14,400 --> 00:31:16,100
It's a matter of mutual respect.

590
00:31:17,500 --> 00:31:19,000
If you don't come back all night

591
00:31:19,000 --> 00:31:19,733
wouldn't I

592
00:31:19,733 --> 00:31:21,467
have to spend the night in anxiety and fear?

593
00:31:27,233 --> 00:31:28,733
I'll let you know next time.

594
00:31:29,967 --> 00:31:31,067
Can I go rest now?

595
00:31:39,767 --> 00:31:40,733
Who is he?

596
00:31:41,433 --> 00:31:42,233
I forgot to tell you.

597
00:31:42,300 --> 00:31:42,833
He's my friend.

598
00:31:44,800 --> 00:31:45,433
Hi

599
00:31:46,000 --> 00:31:46,867
I am Duan Jiaxu.

600
00:31:52,033 --> 00:31:53,667
I heard from Su Haoan

601
00:31:53,667 --> 00:31:56,433
that Sang Yan didn't date a single girl during his four years at university.

602
00:31:56,567 --> 00:31:58,933
He spent all his time hanging out with a campus heartthrob

603
00:31:58,933 --> 00:31:59,967
named Duan Jiaxu.

604
00:32:04,800 --> 00:32:05,633
Duan Jiaxu

605
00:32:06,767 --> 00:32:07,567
I've heard a lot about you.

606
00:32:08,733 --> 00:32:10,400
I also have a flaw:

607
00:32:11,233 --> 00:32:13,267
my safety awareness is stronger than someone else's

608
00:32:13,600 --> 00:32:15,300
and I remember we have a contract clause.

609
00:32:15,600 --> 00:32:16,300
I don't quite recall.

610
00:32:17,967 --> 00:32:19,800
You should inform me in advance before bringing friends home.

611
00:32:19,867 --> 00:32:20,367
All right.

612
00:32:20,400 --> 00:32:21,367
I remember now.

613
00:32:22,467 --> 00:32:23,067
I'm sorry.

614
00:32:24,200 --> 00:32:24,767
It's okay.

615
00:32:25,833 --> 00:32:26,767
We're still getting used

616
00:32:27,033 --> 00:32:28,267
to living together

617
00:32:28,433 --> 00:32:30,267
so small mistakes are excusable.

618
00:32:34,567 --> 00:32:35,633
I'll let it slide this time.

619
00:32:35,633 --> 00:32:36,933
You two catch up.

620
00:32:42,767 --> 00:32:44,367
I told you to leave earlier, but you didn't listen.

621
00:32:45,033 --> 00:32:46,867
You even spilled food on your clothes.

622
00:32:56,933 --> 00:32:58,667
So, where do you think we should go on Thursday?

623
00:32:58,933 --> 00:32:59,567
How about Overtime?

624
00:32:59,933 --> 00:33:00,800
It's opened by Sang Yan.

625
00:33:01,100 --> 00:33:01,933
Sang Yan?

626
00:33:03,100 --> 00:33:04,300
You are still in touch?

627
00:33:04,667 --> 00:33:06,167
I only met him recently

628
00:33:06,400 --> 00:33:07,300
and it was at his gastropub.

629
00:33:07,467 --> 00:33:08,433
So, uh

630
00:33:08,500 --> 00:33:09,733
I need to tell you something.

631
00:33:09,833 --> 00:33:12,233
Remember I told you I have a roommate?

632
00:33:13,400 --> 00:33:14,633
Well, that roommate

633
00:33:15,400 --> 00:33:16,567
is Sang Yan.

634
00:33:17,033 --> 00:33:19,100
He said if we go to his place, he'll give us a discount.

635
00:33:19,367 --> 00:33:21,567
You're actually sharing a place with Sang Yan?

636
00:33:21,933 --> 00:33:23,467
And what discount do we get?

637
00:33:23,833 --> 00:33:24,933
Let's talk about it when we meet.

638
00:33:24,933 --> 00:33:26,367
I still have to get some work done tonight.

639
00:33:26,367 --> 00:33:27,167
I'm going to log off now.

640
00:33:27,400 --> 00:33:29,400
Wait. How much of a discount are we getting?

641
00:33:30,200 --> 00:33:32,400
1 percent.

642
00:33:32,633 --> 00:33:33,833
1 percent?

643
00:33:34,367 --> 00:33:35,600
I'll log off now. Bye.

644
00:33:37,400 --> 00:33:39,000
Wait, did I hear that right?

645
00:33:39,033 --> 00:33:40,900
Is a 1 percent discount still considered a discount?

646
00:33:43,033 --> 00:33:44,267
Let's go with Dian's choice this time.

647
00:33:44,767 --> 00:33:46,233
We've always picked the places before.

648
00:33:46,400 --> 00:33:47,633
It's rare for her to have an opinion.

649
00:33:48,033 --> 00:33:49,067
You're totally on her side, huh?

650
00:33:49,633 --> 00:33:50,500
Wait until we meet

651
00:33:50,500 --> 00:33:52,433
I'll crack open her brain

652
00:33:52,433 --> 00:33:53,800
and see what's going on in there.

653
00:33:54,233 --> 00:33:55,800
Why would she share a place with Sang Yan?

654
00:33:55,967 --> 00:33:56,767
I really don't get it.

655
00:33:58,367 --> 00:33:59,167
It's getting late, Qiao.

656
00:33:59,733 --> 00:34:00,567
You should go to bed now.

657
00:34:02,300 --> 00:34:03,100
All right, then.

658
00:34:03,233 --> 00:34:03,933
Goodnight.

659
00:34:03,933 --> 00:34:04,633
Night.

660
00:34:30,433 --> 00:34:31,000
Hello.

661
00:34:31,100 --> 00:34:32,433
Dian, are you ready?

662
00:34:32,667 --> 00:34:33,200
We're here.

663
00:34:33,400 --> 00:34:34,067
You are already here?

664
00:34:34,100 --> 00:34:35,467
So soon? Just give me a moment.

665
00:34:36,267 --> 00:34:37,033
The car isn't allowed to enter

666
00:34:37,033 --> 00:34:38,200
so I've just parked it at the entrance.

667
00:34:38,433 --> 00:34:40,300
All right, I just finished washing the clothes.

668
00:34:40,300 --> 00:34:41,567
I'll be out as soon as I hang them up.

669
00:34:42,000 --> 00:34:42,833
It's okay. No rush.

670
00:34:42,833 --> 00:34:43,633
Take your time.

671
00:34:44,667 --> 00:34:46,033
Who says there's no rush?

672
00:34:46,033 --> 00:34:46,967
I'm about to die of hunger.

673
00:34:46,967 --> 00:34:48,067
Dian, hurry up.

674
00:34:50,567 --> 00:34:52,233
I'll save your life in a minute. Got to go now.

675
00:34:54,967 --> 00:34:55,667
Hey

676
00:34:56,967 --> 00:34:58,567
did you save a spot for us at Overtime?

677
00:34:59,100 --> 00:35:00,033
We're going to eat first.

678
00:35:00,033 --> 00:35:01,967
We'll be at Overtime around eight.

679
00:35:53,400 --> 00:35:54,333
Are you heading out too?

680
00:36:00,000 --> 00:36:01,367
When did you change your clothes?

681
00:36:14,067 --> 00:36:14,867
Are you going to the garage?

682
00:36:23,167 --> 00:36:23,800
Well...

683
00:36:24,167 --> 00:36:25,467
We haven't reached the basement level yet.

684
00:36:25,467 --> 00:36:26,400
This is the first floor.

685
00:36:35,633 --> 00:36:40,033
[Uptown Flower City]

686
00:36:40,300 --> 00:36:40,800
Let's go.

687
00:36:41,967 --> 00:36:42,467
Dian.

688
00:36:47,000 --> 00:36:47,633
Dian.

689
00:36:48,100 --> 00:36:48,833
It's been a while.

690
00:36:49,067 --> 00:36:49,867
It's been a while.

691
00:36:49,867 --> 00:36:51,433
Why are you two acting shy?

692
00:36:51,567 --> 00:36:53,367
The Nanwu Trio is finally united.

693
00:36:53,367 --> 00:36:55,200
From now on, we'll overcome all obstacles and be invincible.

694
00:36:55,933 --> 00:36:56,633
Who is this?

695
00:37:05,633 --> 00:37:06,500
Is this your boyfriend?

696
00:37:08,633 --> 00:37:09,933
What boyfriend?

697
00:37:09,933 --> 00:37:10,933
This is Xiang Lang.

698
00:37:12,100 --> 00:37:12,800
Xiang Lang.

699
00:37:12,800 --> 00:37:13,700
I remember.

700
00:37:15,667 --> 00:37:16,233
You are from Class 15.

701
00:37:16,300 --> 00:37:16,800
Yes.

702
00:37:16,833 --> 00:37:17,700
- I'm Su Haoan. - Hi.

703
00:37:19,500 --> 00:37:20,233
Sang Yan.

704
00:37:22,367 --> 00:37:22,967
Long time no see.

705
00:37:32,267 --> 00:37:33,600
Didn't we agree that you'd drive your car?

706
00:37:34,700 --> 00:37:35,467
I can't be bothered to drive.

707
00:37:37,033 --> 00:37:37,567
I drove here.

708
00:37:38,100 --> 00:37:38,867
Where do you need to go?

709
00:37:39,600 --> 00:37:40,200
It's fine.

710
00:37:40,633 --> 00:37:42,467
We'll just find somewhere to eat.

711
00:37:42,667 --> 00:37:43,633
Didn't you guys already make plans?

712
00:37:43,633 --> 00:37:44,367
You can go ahead.

713
00:37:45,667 --> 00:37:46,867
We really haven't met in a long time.

714
00:37:47,033 --> 00:37:47,867
We should definitely catch up.

715
00:37:48,600 --> 00:37:49,800
It's been a while since we last met as well.

716
00:37:51,800 --> 00:37:52,967
Why make such a big deal of it?

717
00:37:52,967 --> 00:37:53,867
You're not really close with them.

718
00:37:53,867 --> 00:37:55,167
Even if we're not close, we can still catch up

719
00:37:58,233 --> 00:37:58,800
right?

720
00:37:59,233 --> 00:38:01,333
Yeah. So you want to go with them, right?

721
00:38:02,000 --> 00:38:02,667
Is it all right?

722
00:38:03,700 --> 00:38:04,600
I don't think so.

723
00:38:04,600 --> 00:38:05,800
I think it's pretty all right.

724
00:38:06,133 --> 00:38:06,767
Where's your car?

725
00:38:20,167 --> 00:38:20,800
Open the door.

726
00:38:21,633 --> 00:38:22,500
Yes, boss.

727
00:38:23,967 --> 00:38:25,633
It's amazing how fate works.

728
00:38:25,933 --> 00:38:27,400
You haven't seen a friend in seven or eight years

729
00:38:27,400 --> 00:38:28,333
and then you just run into them like this.

730
00:38:28,600 --> 00:38:30,633
If Sang Yan and Wen Yifan can be roommates

731
00:38:30,633 --> 00:38:32,000
what else is impossible?

732
00:38:32,633 --> 00:38:33,400
Since there are so many of us

733
00:38:33,400 --> 00:38:34,633
I'll tidy up the car first.

734
00:38:34,767 --> 00:38:35,467
I'll help you.

735
00:38:38,333 --> 00:38:39,200
I know

736
00:38:39,367 --> 00:38:40,967
this is definitely something worth bragging about.

737
00:38:41,633 --> 00:38:42,433
What are you talking about?

738
00:38:43,200 --> 00:38:44,700
There's no need to bring up

739
00:38:44,867 --> 00:38:46,367
our shared rental to everyone.

740
00:38:50,967 --> 00:38:52,367
We'll manage if the five of us squeeze a bit.

741
00:38:53,167 --> 00:38:53,800
This should be all right.

742
00:38:55,200 --> 00:38:56,433
Dian, you sit in the passenger seat

743
00:38:56,433 --> 00:38:57,267
and help me with the navigation.

744
00:39:01,767 --> 00:39:02,567
My legs are too long.

745
00:39:02,567 --> 00:39:03,667
It's uncomfortable sitting in the back.

746
00:39:04,067 --> 00:39:04,967
You can just go straight.

747
00:39:09,400 --> 00:39:09,933
Okay.

748
00:39:12,633 --> 00:39:14,033
It's fine, I'll sit in the back.

749
00:39:14,433 --> 00:39:15,267
Is that okay?

750
00:39:15,267 --> 00:39:16,100
Sure. No worries.

751
00:39:46,367 --> 00:39:47,500
I can't see the road with you like this.

752
00:39:47,500 --> 00:39:49,033
Well, then pay attention to the road.

753
00:39:56,433 --> 00:39:57,433
Have you got a girlfriend?

754
00:40:04,500 --> 00:40:05,000
No.

755
00:40:05,800 --> 00:40:07,000
I still haven't met the person I like.

756
00:40:18,167 --> 00:40:19,167
I just thought of a rumor.

757
00:40:21,467 --> 00:40:23,200
Sang Yan, Xiang Lang, and Wen Yifan

758
00:40:23,500 --> 00:40:24,800
they said you three were in a love triangle.

759
00:40:25,000 --> 00:40:25,633
Is it true?

760
00:40:29,500 --> 00:40:30,667
It was all just rumors.

761
00:40:31,400 --> 00:40:32,367
It got passed on

762
00:40:32,767 --> 00:40:34,067
and started to sound like it was real.

763
00:40:34,067 --> 00:40:34,867
It simply wasn't true.

764
00:40:35,267 --> 00:40:36,400
What do you mean by "sound like it was real?"

765
00:40:37,000 --> 00:40:39,000
You're really into gossip and just making things up.

766
00:40:39,200 --> 00:40:40,467
What I'm saying is true.

767
00:40:41,067 --> 00:40:42,000
If you don't believe me, ask Sang Yan.

768
00:40:42,367 --> 00:40:44,067
He even got into a fight over it.

769
00:40:45,333 --> 00:40:46,633
I heard from Zhou Zhiming

770
00:40:46,700 --> 00:40:48,867
that Pretty Face Wen doesn't actually like Sang Yan.

771
00:40:49,167 --> 00:40:51,000
She only got together with him

772
00:40:51,000 --> 00:40:52,200
because he kept pursuing her.

773
00:40:52,933 --> 00:40:54,333
So, when she met someone better

774
00:40:54,333 --> 00:40:55,700
she immediately cheated.

775
00:40:56,033 --> 00:40:57,200
Who's better?

776
00:40:57,667 --> 00:40:58,867
It's Xiang Lang from the class next door.

777
00:41:16,000 --> 00:41:16,800
If I didn't tell you

778
00:41:17,000 --> 00:41:18,933
would you think Pretty Face Wen is this kind of person?

779
00:41:19,067 --> 00:41:21,100
It's really quite disgusting.

780
00:41:21,100 --> 00:41:21,600
Indeed.

781
00:41:21,667 --> 00:41:22,367
But why?

782
00:41:24,367 --> 00:41:26,833
She thinks being good-looking makes her great.

783
00:41:28,100 --> 00:41:29,400
There are a lot of good-looking people out there.

784
00:41:29,767 --> 00:41:30,767
Surely they won't all act like this.

785
00:41:30,767 --> 00:41:31,467
Let me tell you this.

786
00:41:31,767 --> 00:41:32,800
With an attitude like yours

787
00:41:32,833 --> 00:41:34,600
what's the point of being pretty?

788
00:41:39,100 --> 00:41:39,667
Apologize.

789
00:41:39,667 --> 00:41:40,367
I'm sorry.

790
00:41:41,800 --> 00:41:42,933
I'm not asking you to apologize.

791
00:41:44,000 --> 00:41:44,700
Zhou Zhiming

792
00:41:45,700 --> 00:41:46,500
do I need to teach you?

793
00:41:47,000 --> 00:41:47,867
I won't apologize.

794
00:41:50,100 --> 00:41:51,600
I was just joking earlier

795
00:41:51,667 --> 00:41:53,433
and I'm not the only one saying this.

796
00:41:53,567 --> 00:41:54,433
Joking?

797
00:41:55,067 --> 00:41:56,367
You're a man with such a sharp tongue

798
00:41:56,767 --> 00:41:57,767
aren't you embarrassed?

799
00:41:58,467 --> 00:41:59,767
Let me make this clear today.

800
00:42:00,367 --> 00:42:02,500
If anyone dares spread such rumors again

801
00:42:03,033 --> 00:42:04,200
the consequences will be the same as his.

802
00:42:05,400 --> 00:42:06,633
I don't have many hobbies.

803
00:42:07,700 --> 00:42:08,700
I just like holding grudges.

804
00:42:09,700 --> 00:42:10,200
Talk.

805
00:42:10,800 --> 00:42:11,667
Pretty Face Wen...

806
00:42:11,667 --> 00:42:12,267
No

807
00:42:12,267 --> 00:42:13,167
Wen Yifan

808
00:42:13,967 --> 00:42:14,700
I'm sorry.

809
00:42:15,200 --> 00:42:18,500
It was me who told others you were cheating

810
00:42:18,500 --> 00:42:19,600
but I had no proof.

811
00:42:19,633 --> 00:42:20,700
I was just making things up.

812
00:42:20,800 --> 00:42:22,067
I won't say it again in the future.

813
00:42:22,433 --> 00:42:23,100
Is that enough?

814
00:42:23,333 --> 00:42:24,000
Can you let me go now?

815
00:42:34,867 --> 00:42:35,433
What about me?

816
00:42:36,567 --> 00:42:37,400
Am I not also a victim?

817
00:42:38,667 --> 00:42:39,567
Sang Yan

818
00:42:40,633 --> 00:42:41,333
I'm sorry.

819
00:42:43,833 --> 00:42:44,633
Why are you a victim?

820
00:42:47,467 --> 00:42:49,767
Can you spread rumors according to the facts?

821
00:42:50,500 --> 00:42:52,100
What do you mean the other person found someone better

822
00:42:52,100 --> 00:42:53,033
and dumped me?

823
00:42:53,633 --> 00:42:56,567
If I were actually pursuing them that hard

824
00:42:57,333 --> 00:42:58,967
they'd be completely

825
00:42:58,967 --> 00:43:00,467
captivated by me.

826
00:43:02,000 --> 00:43:02,567
Understand?

827
00:43:05,400 --> 00:43:05,900
Yes.

828
00:43:06,067 --> 00:43:06,767
Louder.

829
00:43:07,633 --> 00:43:08,167
Yes!

830
00:43:22,667 --> 00:43:23,267
Thank you.

831
00:43:24,567 --> 00:43:26,200
He doesn't even know who's better.

832
00:43:29,467 --> 00:43:30,367
Sang Yan has always been

833
